	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>unnamed konami boards</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />so i opened up a silent service cart today thinking it was an UNROM board, but to my surprise, it was unmarked.  It only had "Konami" written on it and didnt have a capacitor on the right side.  I checked the rom and it says that it is an UNROM game.  will this work when i try to make a repro?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Wed Apr 18, 2007 12:14 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does it look anything like <a href="http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/nes_discrete/NES_UNROM.html" class="postlink">this</a>? If your board has the 74HC32 and 74HC161 chips, I guess you can be sure it is an UNROM board. I've seen some weird UNROM boards, and a while ago <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=2849" class="postlink">I even made a devcart</a> out of a weird board where the PRG ROM was placed vertically, unlike most other carts. As you can see from the pictures, this is a Konami board too.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Wed Apr 18, 2007 12:29 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Konami made its own UNROM-compatible boards in some markets. I seem to remember that some game publishers were allowed to do this to help stave off the effects of the "ROM shortage". <a href="http://www.bripro.com/low/hardware/devcarts/txt/boardtable.txt" class="postlink">Boardtable</a> lists a lot of games as "351258", and <a href="http://www.parodius.com/~veilleux/boardnames" class="postlink">boardnames</a> lists 351258 as an UNROM clone.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


